def: A whitener; a bleacher; a whitester. [Obs.]The whitsters in Datchet mead. Shak.
Having a thick and bushy head of hair.

A kind of lichen (Cetraria Icelandica) found from the Arcticregions to the North Temperate zone. It furnishes a nutritious jellyand other forms of food, and is used in pulmonary complaints as ademulcent.
Verbal legerdemain; a playing with words. [R.] Coleridge.
Having the form of a drop. Owen.
Containing or impregnated with benzoin; as, benzoinated lard.
A prefix meaning against, opposite or opposed to, contrary, orin place of; -- used in composition in many English words. It isoften shortened to ant-; as, antacid, antarctic.
The whole interior portion of a vessel below the lower deck, inwhich the cargo is stowed.
A person of a dull, grave, gloomy temperament. W. browne.
To weary or tire out; to fatigue. [R.] Sir T. Herbert.
To put in, or as in, a hearse or coffin. Shak.
